A reality check for robots business; expect consensus earnings cuts; downgrade to UW

Tuopu's share price has been on a roller- coaster ride this year, with the stock rallying \(56\%\) year to Feb- peak (vs. CSI300 - \(1\%\) ) driven by market enthusiasm for humanoid robotics. It then dropped \(42\%\) to a YTD- low in mid- July (CSI300 \(+4\%\) ) on heightened tariff tensions, sluggish Tesla sales and disappointing 1Q25 earnings, before rebounding \(35\%\) to date (CSI300 \(+11\%\) ). We downgraded Tuopu from OW to Neutral in Oct- 2024 on concerns of potential tariff hikes and slower- than- expected Tesla orders. We then upgraded to OW on sequential improvement from key customers Tesla and Seres post 1Q results. We now expect consensus earnings cuts post the 2Q25 result, which was a miss vs. JPM and the Street. We cut our 2025/26E earnings by \(20 - 26\%\) and are now \(18 - 23\%\) below the Street. We downgrade the stock to UW with a PT of Rmb40. In China's auto part value chain, we like Fuyao Glass and Minth.

- 2Q25 seeing sequential improvement. As we highlighted in our Jun-2025 upgrade note, Tuopu's top customers Tesla (33% of revenue) and Seres (17-18% of revenue) had both seen sequential sales improvement in 2Q25. As a result, Tuopu's 2Q25 revenue saw 24% q/q and 10% y/y growth (vs. 1Q25 1% y/y). While NPM sustained at above 10% in 2Q25 and also a sequential improvement vs. 1Q25, it was below 1H24's 11-12%, leading net profit to a 10% y/y decline.

- However, we expect Street estimate cuts post results. While Tesla's newly launched Model YL is seeing some traction in China, the automaker's global delivery was -13% in 1H25 and J.P. Morgan analyst Ryan Brinkman expects a full year 2025 decline of 11%. We now expect Tuopu's revenue to see only 8% growth in 2H25 with flatish earnings in 2H25 vs. 2H24.

- Humanoid robotic business segment result was somewhat disappointing. The segment's revenue grew 22% y/y and only 7% h/h in 1H25, with GPM contracting to 30.5% vs. 51% in 2024. We cut our estimates on robotic segment revenue in 2H25 but keep 2026-27 unchanged for now.

- Into 2026, we prefer component players with higher exposure to overseas markets. In 2026, China auto sales are likely to see no growth or potentially a decline given policy expiration. On the other hand, US and EU auto sales may see recovery along with interest rate cuts. We prefer players with high overseas exposure. Tuopu still derives >75% of revenue from the domestic market in 1H25 (see Table 5 for Chinese auto part players' revenue breakdown by region).
- We downgrade Tuopu to UW with a Jun-26 PT of Rmb40 based on SOTP (40x PER for robots and 20x PER for auto parts, unchanged multiples vs. our previous PT).

Ningbo Tuopu Group Co Ltd (Underweight; Price Target: Rmb40.00)

We like Tuopu's position as a tier- 0.5 parts supplier and its ability to expand substantially through self- developed products. Tuopu is gradually stepping out of Tesla's shadow by lowering the revenue contribution from Tesla thanks to the robust growth of other domestic NEV customers. We downgrade Tuopu to UW post earnings miss in 1Q/2Q25.

We cut our PT to Rmb40 and extend it to Jun- 26, based on SOTP, applying 40x PER for robots and 20x PER for auto parts (unchanged multiples vs. our previous PT of Rmb56). We summarize our SOTP valuation below:
